        "description": {
            "value": "<p>A swirling vortex flash freezes the air, dealing 10d8 cold damage. Each creature in the area must attempt a Fortitude save.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes half damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes full damage and is @UUID[Compendium.sf2e.conditions.Item.Slowed]{Slowed 1} until the start of your next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature takes double damage, is @UUID[Compendium.sf2e.conditions.Item.Immobilized] by a layer of ice, and is slowed 1 as long as it's immobilized. The ice is an object with 50 Hit Points, Hardness 5, immunity to cold damage, and vulnerability 10 to fire. It has object immunities and is destroyed if the target Escapes.</p><hr /><p><strong>Heightened (+1)</strong> The damage increases by 1d8 and the ice's Hit Points increase by 5.</p>"
